    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="update-date">Last Updated: October 26, 2024</p>

    <p>This privacy policy applies to the <strong>VoiceScroll</strong> mobile application. By using our application, you consent to the collection and use of information as described in this policy.</p>

    <h2>1. Accessibility Services (Crucial Disclosure)</h2>
    <p>VoiceScroll uses the <strong>AccessibilityService API</strong> to enable core features for users. This API is used exclusively for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Automated Scrolling:</strong> To perform vertical and horizontal "scroll" and "swipe" gestures based on user voice commands or manual button triggers.</li>
        <li><strong>System Actions:</strong> To execute the "Back" button function via voice command.</li>
        <li><strong>Touch Interaction:</strong> To simulate "Click/Tap" gestures on the center of the screen as requested by the user.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="disclaimer-box">
        <strong>Data Privacy Guarantee:</strong> We value your privacy above all. VoiceScroll <strong>DOES NOT</strong> use Accessibility Services to collect, record, monitor, or transmit any personal data, screen content, or user information. All gesture processing is performed locally and temporarily on your device only to execute your commands.
    </div>

    <h2>2. Speech Recognition</h2>
    <p>VoiceScroll utilizes the device's built-in <strong>Speech Recognition</strong> engine to process voice commands. Voice data is processed through the system's standard speech-to-text API (provided by Google). We do not record, store, or upload your voice data to any external servers.</p>

    <h2>3. Advertising and Analytics</h2>
    <p>We use third-party services to display advertisements and monitor app stability. These services may access your Advertising ID:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Google AdMob:</strong> For displaying personalized or non-personalized ads. <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank">View Policy</a></li>
        <li><strong>Firebase Crashlytics & Analytics:</strong> To identify technical bugs and analyze app usage to improve performance. <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank">View Policy</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. In-App Purchases</h2>
    <p>Premium features are provided through the <strong>Google Play Billing System</strong>. All payment transactions and sensitive financial information are handled securely by Google Play. The developer does not have access to your credit card or billing details.</p>

    <h2>5. Network Access</h2>
    <p>Internet access is used for checking app updates, loading advertisements, and verifying your Premium status through Google Play Services.</p>

    <h2>6. Disclaimer of Liability</h2>
    <p>The use of this application is at your own risk. The developer is not responsible for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Damage caused by the use or inability to use the App.</li>
        <li>Technical malfunctions of communication networks or terminal performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Unexpected actions caused by "scroll gestures" interacting with other applications.</strong></li>
        <li>Any impact on background functions of the device.</li>
    </ul>

